76
00:06:35,561 --> 00:06:36,562
Is that right?

77
00:06:37,563 --> 00:06:39,899
-Yes.
-He didn't send this guy.

78
00:06:39,982 --> 00:06:43,027
He's here
because he wants the land in Songtan.

79
00:06:43,820 --> 00:06:47,782
Is it really bad for our son
if we refuse to sell it

80
00:06:47,865 --> 00:06:49,408
and hold onto it?

81
00:06:50,326 --> 00:06:52,703
He's just saying that.

82
00:06:52,787 --> 00:06:56,124
What Minister doesn't own
a little plot of land?

83
00:06:56,207 --> 00:06:59,627
Why would he get in trouble?
He's such a coward.

84
00:06:59,710 --> 00:07:02,421
My gosh. He must have his reasons.

85
00:07:04,507 --> 00:07:08,052
Sir, technically,
it isn't just a little plot of land.

86
00:07:08,803 --> 00:07:11,013
You have 30,000 pyeong
of registered farmland.

87
00:07:11,097 --> 00:07:13,850
But you neither live there
nor farm the land.

88
00:07:14,851 --> 00:07:17,353
It's only because
I'm not strong enough to.

89
00:07:17,437 --> 00:07:19,021
It's a violation of the Farmland Act.

90
00:07:19,647 --> 00:07:22,108
I don't know how he passed the hearing,

91
00:07:22,191 --> 00:07:23,818
but this cannot…

92
00:07:24,485 --> 00:07:25,778
go unnoticed forever.

93
00:07:26,404 --> 00:07:29,240
This is a ticking time bomb
for a public official.

94
00:07:30,616 --> 00:07:31,534
A bomb?

95
00:07:31,617 --> 00:07:33,995
You've seen several Ministers
who were removed from office

96
00:07:34,078 --> 00:07:35,371
for making bad land deals.

97
00:07:38,416 --> 00:07:39,959
Sir. Ma'am.

98
00:07:40,543 --> 00:07:41,419
You're right.

99
00:07:42,420 --> 00:07:43,921
I want your land in Songtan.

100
00:07:44,839 --> 00:07:48,468
But the reason I came all the way here
is that it's so clear

101
00:07:49,010 --> 00:07:52,096
that the land will be an obstacle
to the Minister's political career.

102
00:07:52,847 --> 00:07:54,599
As someone who respects him,

103
00:07:55,141 --> 00:07:57,143
I'd like to prevent anything
that could harm him.

104
00:08:03,441 --> 00:08:05,401
We'll buy it for 58 billion won.

105
00:08:08,946 --> 00:08:11,240
Did the value go up that much?

106
00:08:11,324 --> 00:08:14,452
I know you're not greedy about money.
I can tell.

107
00:08:15,286 --> 00:08:16,579
But 58 billion won…

108
00:08:17,705 --> 00:08:21,292
You can imagine how you can spend
your retirement with that, can't you?

109
00:08:21,375 --> 00:08:24,170
Must you ruin your son's life

110
00:08:24,253 --> 00:08:26,255
and keep that land

111
00:08:26,339 --> 00:08:28,341
just because it's where your ancestors
were buried?

112
00:08:29,175 --> 00:08:32,470
Ma'am. We have many sick people
in our hospital.

113
00:08:33,012 --> 00:08:37,058
Those patients have nowhere to go
because the hospital is too small.

114
00:08:38,309 --> 00:08:39,519
Please.

115
00:08:40,019 --> 00:08:44,190
Let us build our hospital
on your land in Songtan.

116
00:08:56,244 --> 00:08:57,620
Goodness.

117
00:09:05,503 --> 00:09:07,380
Thank you for breakfast, ma'am.

118
00:09:13,469 --> 00:09:16,264
Oh, dear. You hardly ate at all.

119
00:09:17,390 --> 00:09:20,434
Make sure to eat something later.

120
00:09:20,518 --> 00:09:21,394
Don't skip your meal.

121
00:09:33,823 --> 00:09:36,659
You know smoking is bad for you.

122
00:09:36,742 --> 00:09:40,162
What are you talking about?
I quit smoking years ago.

123
00:09:44,750 --> 00:09:46,085
It's nice here.

124
00:09:47,461 --> 00:09:50,590
Of course, it must look nice to outsiders.

125
00:09:51,841 --> 00:09:53,968
If you bought a house in Seoul
and came here to visit,

126
00:09:54,051 --> 00:09:55,303
it would look nicer to you, too.

127
00:09:59,307 --> 00:10:00,474
A long time ago,

128
00:10:01,350 --> 00:10:03,853
this used to be a total wasteland.

129
00:10:04,520 --> 00:10:07,356
The townspeople cultivated
this wasteland together with bare hands.

130
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:08,733
All of this.

131
00:10:09,358 --> 00:10:10,443
How incredible.

132
00:10:11,569 --> 00:10:13,279
It wasn't out of choice.

133
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:17,116
If we didn't, they whipped us.
If we ran, they shot us.

134
00:10:17,199 --> 00:10:18,576
We did it to stay alive.

135
00:10:19,493 --> 00:10:22,622
I was dragged here
all the way from Pohang.

136
00:10:23,164 --> 00:10:24,707
The soldiers

137
00:10:25,750 --> 00:10:28,419
put their submachine guns on our backs

138
00:10:28,502 --> 00:10:30,212
and shoved us into the huts.

139
00:10:31,088 --> 00:10:34,550
What era are you talking about?
During the Japanese occupation?

140
00:10:34,634 --> 00:10:36,218
Japanese occupation?

141
00:10:36,302 --> 00:10:39,180
If I worked here back then,
I'd be over 100 years old now.

142
00:10:39,805 --> 00:10:41,891
How ancient do you think I am?

143
00:10:52,068 --> 00:10:53,527
They abused us for years,

144
00:10:54,570 --> 00:10:58,282
but we still worked hard because we were
promised some of the land we reclaimed.

145
00:10:58,908 --> 00:11:00,534
But now, they say the government owns it.

146
00:11:01,494 --> 00:11:03,162
They're telling us to give it back.

147
00:11:05,122 --> 00:11:06,082
You know,

148
00:11:06,582 --> 00:11:09,210
I was a bit of a thug back in the day.

149
00:11:12,129 --> 00:11:14,507
But still, my dad protected that land
in Songtan

150
00:11:14,590 --> 00:11:17,385
until the very end and left it to me.

151
00:11:20,638 --> 00:11:23,808
I wanted to live there with everyone here.

152
00:11:25,393 --> 00:11:26,769
I cannot do anything here

153
00:11:27,520 --> 00:11:30,356
since they keep reminding me how all
the land belongs to the government.

154
00:11:31,482 --> 00:11:34,443
Everyone? Live together in Songtan?

155
00:11:34,527 --> 00:11:35,903
All the townspeople?

156
00:11:35,986 --> 00:11:39,740
It's not like there are that many.

157
00:11:39,824 --> 00:11:42,493
It's a huge plot of land.
You can all go there.

158
00:11:43,202 --> 00:11:45,704
Or you can just keep 1,000 pyeong
and sell the rest.

159
00:11:45,788 --> 00:11:49,041
Or you can buy better land
with the money from the sale

160
00:11:49,125 --> 00:11:50,584
and have everyone move there.

161
00:11:53,295 --> 00:11:55,089
My second son won't allow it.

162
00:11:55,756 --> 00:11:57,633
He'd blow his fuse.

163
00:11:57,716 --> 00:12:01,262
He said he would rather kill himself
than have people find out

164
00:12:01,804 --> 00:12:03,639
that I was one of the pioneers.

165
00:12:06,809 --> 00:12:09,770
But will he really be in trouble…

166
00:12:12,064 --> 00:12:13,482
