00:26:34,718 --> 00:26:36,511
Why don't you leave these here?

347
00:26:36,594 --> 00:26:38,680
I saw on my way up here

348
00:26:38,763 --> 00:26:42,517
that the bakery on the first floor
has the best location.

349
00:26:42,600 --> 00:26:44,019
It's the perfect size for us, too.

350
00:26:44,102 --> 00:26:45,603
I will take that into consideration.

351
00:26:45,687 --> 00:26:48,982
I'll let our president know
that you said you'll consider the idea

352
00:26:49,065 --> 00:26:51,234
and look it over. Thank you for your time.

353
00:27:01,828 --> 00:27:02,912
Put those away.

354
00:27:02,996 --> 00:27:04,122
Okay.

355
00:27:13,923 --> 00:27:15,425
Don't take those things. Just exercise.

356
00:27:19,971 --> 00:27:23,475
Hwajeong Life Insurance said they'll buy
the data sets at 1.5 million won each.

357
00:27:23,558 --> 00:27:25,185
Why did he bother fighting it?

358
00:27:27,395 --> 00:27:30,315
Draft a contract with Hwajeong Chemical
stating that we get a 30% commission

359
00:27:30,398 --> 00:27:32,067
on sales made through our hospital.

360
00:27:32,150 --> 00:27:32,984
Okay.

361
00:27:34,235 --> 00:27:37,614
And let me see the lease status
of the businesses in the hospital.

362
00:27:37,697 --> 00:27:38,907
Okay.

363
00:27:42,827 --> 00:27:44,371
GLUTTON: MOST SEEM TO WANT A STRIKE

364
00:27:44,454 --> 00:27:45,914
WORKER ANT: LET'S MEET UP

365
00:27:48,583 --> 00:27:50,502
What's wrong? It wasn't your fault.

366
00:27:51,961 --> 00:27:53,713
Are you trying to make me feel guilty?

367
00:27:55,423 --> 00:27:58,301
Because that cop got hurt
after I sent the patient with him?

368
00:28:07,936 --> 00:28:08,853
No.

369
00:28:10,605 --> 00:28:12,399
I was reminded of a patient from before.

370
00:28:13,858 --> 00:28:15,485
I made a call to discharge that patient…

371
00:28:17,612 --> 00:28:19,072
"Do you remember that patient?"

372
00:28:20,907 --> 00:28:21,825
Pardon?

373
00:28:22,742 --> 00:28:25,120
-Are you asking me?
-During my residency,

374
00:28:31,292 --> 00:28:33,753
I was supposed to call a cardiologist,

375
00:28:34,796 --> 00:28:37,298
but it was obvious that the patient
had congestive heart failure.

376
00:28:39,134 --> 00:28:41,511
He had difficulty breathing
due to the blood in his lungs.

377
00:28:42,011 --> 00:28:43,555
I could tell just from the stethoscope.

378
00:28:45,640 --> 00:28:49,060
I prescribed him aspirin and diuretics,
and he got better in no time.

379
00:28:50,687 --> 00:28:51,896
I felt good.

380
00:28:51,980 --> 00:28:53,231
Did you discharge him?

381
00:28:54,566 --> 00:28:55,442
Yes.

382
00:28:56,651 --> 00:28:57,861
It was late,

383
00:28:57,944 --> 00:29:00,572
and I didn't want to hear the specialist
whine about being called in.

384
00:29:02,574 --> 00:29:03,616
They're all excuses.

385
00:29:05,452 --> 00:29:06,327
I think…

386
00:29:07,370 --> 00:29:09,622
I needed reassurance
that I can do it on my own

387
00:29:11,166 --> 00:29:12,542
at the time.

388
00:29:16,921 --> 00:29:18,923
The next day, Ms. Kim asked me
when I was leaving,

389
00:29:19,924 --> 00:29:21,593
"Do you remember that patient?"

390
00:29:22,260 --> 00:29:25,388
Do you remember that patient?
He came back.

391
00:29:25,472 --> 00:29:26,473
"He came back."

392
00:29:29,976 --> 00:29:33,021
Lee Gang-min died four or five days later.

393
00:29:37,275 --> 00:29:38,401
That wasn't…

394
00:29:39,402 --> 00:29:40,779
necessarily your fault.

395
00:29:42,614 --> 00:29:44,032
I hate that question.

396
00:29:45,325 --> 00:29:46,576
"Do you remember that patient?"

397
00:29:48,036 --> 00:29:49,120
"He came back."

398
00:29:53,625 --> 00:29:54,793
How did you feel?

399
00:30:03,802 --> 00:30:05,887
I couldn't tell anybody in our department.

400
00:30:07,931 --> 00:30:09,265
Not because of the consequences,

401
00:30:09,808 --> 00:30:12,644
but because I knew they would feel
uncomfortable to hear about my mistake.

402
00:30:13,937 --> 00:30:15,522
They tried to avoid me.

403
00:30:16,439 --> 00:30:19,567
People in this field
do not admit to mistakes.

404
00:30:20,527 --> 00:30:23,154
It's impossible not to make them,
but they insist they don't.

405
00:30:26,616 --> 00:30:29,869
Doctors must admit to their mistakes, too.

406
00:30:31,871 --> 00:30:32,789
But…

407
00:30:35,708 --> 00:30:37,293
It's true, but if you do…

408
00:30:37,377 --> 00:30:39,170
It's a good thing to remember patients.

409
00:30:41,256 --> 00:30:42,966
It'll reduce the number of mistakes
you make.

410
00:30:47,971 --> 00:30:48,930
Good night.

411
00:31:09,284 --> 00:31:10,118
Over here.

412
00:31:15,415 --> 00:31:16,833
Gosh.

413
00:31:20,420 --> 00:31:22,672
One serving of tako wasabi, please.
The sake is good here.

414
00:31:23,715 --> 00:31:25,133
And Daiginjo sake and grilled squid.

415
00:31:26,926 --> 00:31:29,262
We'll also have grilled smelt.

416
00:31:29,345 --> 00:31:30,263
Okay.

